2026-03-07 00:35:51.922 [boundedElastic-1] DEBUG c.i.m.t.service.TargetProcessService - Response status=200 body={"Next":"https://satispay.tpondemand.com/api/v1/UserStories/?include=[Id,Name,Description,Project[Id,Name],EntityState[Id,Name],CreateDate,Owner[Id,Login]]&where=Owner.Login eq 'aldo.lushkja@satispay.com'&orderByDesc=CreateDate&format=json&take=10&skip=10","Items":[{"ResourceType":"UserStory","Id":215663,"Name":"Consumer Deboarding from Satispay Plus","Description":"<!--markdown-->## Why\n\nThe standard unsubscription flow is consumer-initiated and constrained by a status transition matrix. There are situations where Satispay must act unilaterally, regardless of the consumer's current state:\n\n- **Compliance / Legal** — a regulatory body requires immediate removal.\n- **Fraud / Abuse** — subscription must be terminated and any refundable amount returned.\n- **Operational** — a back-office operator needs to correct a mis-subscription or unblock a stuck state.\n- **Event-driven** — an upstream service (fraud engine, account closure) triggers deboarding automatically.\n\n`UNSUBSCRIBED` is not sufficient because it requires passing through intermediate states that may not be reachable, and does not distinguish an admin-forced removal from a voluntary exit.\n\n---\n\n## What\n\n### New terminal state: `DEBOARDED`\n\n- **Terminal** — no further transitions possible.\n- **Bypass-only** — not reachable via the normal transition matrix.\n- **Semantically distinct from `UNSUBSCRIBED`** — signals administrative removal; downstream SNS consumers can act on it differently.\n\n### New internal endpoint\n\n```\nPOST /v1/consumers/deboard\n{ \"consumer_id\": \"<uuid>\" }\n```\n\nScoped to `/v1/consumers` because the caller identifies a consumer. Designed to be called manually by operators, by other microservices, and reusable by a future SQS listener with no changes to core logic.\n\n### On a successful deboard, the system:\n\n1. Revokes all `SCHEDULED` charges.\n2. Computes and issues a refund (full within 14 days, pro-rata for yearly plans, zero for monthly past the window).\n3. Updates the `DONE` charge with refund metadata.\n4. Ends any active consumer discount.\n5. Persists the subscription as `DEBOARDED` with `valid_to = now`.\n6. Publishes an SNS notification with status `DEBOARDED`.\n7. Cancels any active external partner memberships linked to the subscription.\n\nThe entire operation is atomic — any failure rolls back completely.\n\n### Sequence Diagram\n\n\n![diagram-plus-deboard.jpg](https://satispay.tpondemand.com/Attachment.aspx?AttachmentID=52817)\n\n### Error cases\n\n| Code | HTTP | Condition |\n|------|------|-----------|\n| SP_002 | 400 | `consumer_id` missing or malformed |\n| SP_005 | 404 | No subscription found for the consumer |\n| SP_033 | 409 | Subscription already in a terminal state |\n","CreateDate":"\/Date(1772815400000+0100)\/","Owner":{"ResourceType":"GeneralUser","Id":978,"Login":"aldo.lushkja@satispay.com"},"Project":{"ResourceType":"Project","Id":186131,"Name":"[IT-B] Satispay Plus"},"EntityState":{"ResourceType":"EntityState","Id":73,"Name":"Open"}},{"ResourceType":"UserStory","Id":215551,"Name":"Analyze S+ Code Distribution Engine Upload","Description":"<!--markdown-->## Context\nWe are expanding our Premium plan value proposition by integrating multiple third-party partners. To access these services (e.g., Corriere della Sera, Dott, WeRoad), consumers are required to present specific redemption codes or unique links.\n\n## WHY \nWe must ensure these codes are visible and accessible to consumers directly within their Premium Plans UI. As we currently lack a centralized system to manage this, we need a dedicated Code Distribution Engine that allows users to visualize, copy, and redeem (\"riscattarlo\") these codes to start using the partner services for free. Without this, the value of the partnerships remains inaccessible to the user.\n\n## WHAT\n\nWe need to build a Code Distribution Engine that ingests lists of codes provided by partners and distributes them to eligible consumers (specifically premium plan subscribers).\n\n### Core Requirements:\n\n- One-to-One Allocation: For any given partner list, a consumer holds up to 1 active code at a time.\n- Multi-Partner Support: The system must handle distributing multiple codes from different partners simultaneously to the same user (e.g., a user sees a code for Corriere, a code for Dott, and a code for WeRoad all at once).\n- Plan-Based Segmentation: We must be able to configure which Premium plans grant access to which codes (e.g., a \"Plus\" subscriber gets access to Dott, but only a higher-tier subscriber might get access to Komoot).\n- Frequency & Rotation: The engine must support time-based distribution logic, allowing codes to be refreshed or changed on a specific frequency (e.g., a new code generated every X days).\n- Format Flexibility: The system must distinguish between and support both:\nAlphanumerical codes (text to copy).\nDirect redemption links (clickable URLs).\n\n### Nice to Have (High Priority):\n\n- Redemption History: A visible log for the consumer showing the history of all previously distributed/redeemed codes.","CreateDate":"\/Date(1772797926000+0100)\/","Owner":{"ResourceType":"GeneralUser","Id":978,"Login":"aldo.lushkja@satispay.com"},"Project":{"ResourceType":"Project","Id":186131,"Name":"[IT-B] Satispay Plus"},"EntityState":{"ResourceType":"EntityState","Id":76,"Name":"In Testing"}},{"ResourceType":"UserStory","Id":215101,"Name":"[satispay_plus][prod] Enforce consumer_id and subscription_id check","Description":"<!--markdown--># WHY\n\nTo enforce security checks for consumer_id and subscription_id pair.\n\n# WHAT\n\nExecute the following cURL:\n\n```curl\n curl --request POST \\    \n    --url https://internal-admin-api.satispay.aws/consumer/satispay-plus/v1/configurations/ \\\n    --header 'Content-Type: application/json' \\                                                                                                                                                                \n    --header 'User-Agent: insomnia/11.2.0' \\\n    --data '{\"key\":\"SUBSCRIPTION_CONSUMER_ID_VALIDATION_ENABLED\",\"value\":\"true\"}'  \n```","CreateDate":"\/Date(1772553669000+0100)\/","Owner":{"ResourceType":"GeneralUser","Id":978,"Login":"aldo.lushkja@satispay.com"},"Project":{"ResourceType":"Project","Id":140686,"Name":"[IT] Consumer Data Migration"},"EntityState":{"ResourceType":"EntityState","Id":465,"Name":"Done"}},{"ResourceType":"UserStory","Id":214660,"Name":"Add count mismatch cloud watch event","Description":"<!--markdown--># WHY\n\nIn order to enforce robustness of the flow (query -> s3 upload ) is useful to monitor count mismatching.\n\n# WHAT\n\nSend CloudWatch PARTNER_EXPORT_COUNT_MISMATCH event when count of expected (query from `createRecords` job) mismatch with count of exported (s3 upload query from `exporterJob` )","CreateDate":"\/Date(1772202786000+0100)\/","Owner":{"ResourceType":"GeneralUser","Id":978,"Login":"aldo.lushkja@satispay.com"},"Project":{"ResourceType":"Project","Id":186131,"Name":"[IT-B] Satispay Plus"},"EntityState":{"ResourceType":"EntityState","Id":77,"Name":"Done"}},{"ResourceType":"UserStory","Id":214654,"Name":"Changes requested 26/02","Description":"<!--markdown--># WHY\n\nAfter receiving the response from Allianz in 26/02 via email for the past 7 uploads send in production.\n\n# WHAT\n\n- Use \",\" for decimal separator with 2 numbers precision for decimal numbers.\n- Use \"_\" as filler for empty columns.\n\n","CreateDate":"\/Date(1772201222000+0100)\/","Owner":{"ResourceType":"GeneralUser","Id":978,"Login":"aldo.lushkja@satispay.com"},"Project":{"ResourceType":"Project","Id":186131,"Name":"[IT-B] Satispay Plus"},"EntityState":{"ResourceType":"EntityState","Id":77,"Name":"Done"}},{"ResourceType":"UserStory","Id":214073,"Name":"[consumer_loyalty][prod] Business Premium 25-02-2026 - 20_30x","Description":"<!--markdown--># WHY\n\nWe need to enable the 20x and 30x multiplier for this merchants registered to Business Premium.\n\n# WHAT\n\nEnable Business Premium campaigns using PostmanRunner with the csv below and the cURL command:\n\n- csv - [bp_25_02_2026_20x_30x_cleaned_updated.csv](https://satispay.tpondemand.com/Attachment.aspx?AttachmentID=52365)\n\n- cURL command:\n\n```\ncurl --location 'https://internal-admin-api.satispay.aws/consumer/consumer-loyalty/v1/campaigns/' \\\n  --header 'Content-Type: application/json' \\\n  --header 'User-Agent: insomnia/11.2.0' \\\n  --data '{\n      \"entity_id\": \"{{Merchant_ID}}\",\n      \"entity_type\": \"MERCHANT\",\n      \"start_date\": \"2026-02-26T14:00:00.000Z\",\n      \"end_date\": \"2027-02-26T14:00:00.000Z\",\n      \"value\": {{Multiplier}}\n  }'\n```","CreateDate":"\/Date(1772027586000+0100)\/","Owner":{"ResourceType":"GeneralUser","Id":978,"Login":"aldo.lushkja@satispay.com"},"Project":{"ResourceType":"Project","Id":140686,"Name":"[IT] Consumer Data Migration"},"EntityState":{"ResourceType":"EntityState","Id":465,"Name":"Done"}},{"ResourceType":"UserStory","Id":214055,"Name":"[consumer_loyalty][prod] Business Premium 25-02-2026 - 10x","Description":"<!--markdown--># WHY\n\nWe need to enable the 10x multiplier for this merchants registered to Business Premium.\n\n# WHAT\n\nEnable Business Premium campaigns using PostmanRunner with the csv below and the cURL command:\n\n- csv - [bp_25_02_2025_10x_cleaned.csv](https://satispay.tpondemand.com/Attachment.aspx?AttachmentID=52317)\n\n- cURL command:\n\n```\ncurl --location 'https://internal-admin-api.satispay.aws/consumer/consumer-loyalty/v1/campaigns/' \\\n  --header 'Content-Type: application/json' \\\n  --header 'User-Agent: insomnia/11.2.0' \\\n  --data '{\n      \"entity_id\": \"{{merchant_uid}}\",\n      \"entity_type\": \"MERCHANT\",\n      \"start_date\": \"2026-02-26T14:00:00.000Z\",\n      \"end_date\": \"2027-02-26T14:00:00.000Z\",\n      \"value\": 1000\n  }'\n```","CreateDate":"\/Date(1772026987000+0100)\/","Owner":{"ResourceType":"GeneralUser","Id":978,"Login":"aldo.lushkja@satispay.com"},"Project":{"ResourceType":"Project","Id":140686,"Name":"[IT] Consumer Data Migration"},"EntityState":{"ResourceType":"EntityState","Id":465,"Name":"Done"}},{"ResourceType":"UserStory","Id":213754,"Name":"Allianz backfill with parametric date","Description":"<!--markdown--># WHY\n\nAs per product requirements we need to make `activation_date` for the export record in insurance Allianz flow for the already subscribed users using backfill jobs parametric.\n\n# WHAT\n\nWhen backfilling subscribed/grace_period users we need to update `subscriptionBean.validFrom` with the current date or the configured date.","CreateDate":"\/Date(1771865010000+0100)\/","Owner":{"ResourceType":"GeneralUser","Id":978,"Login":"aldo.lushkja@satispay.com"},"Project":{"ResourceType":"Project","Id":186131,"Name":"[IT-B] Satispay Plus"},"EntityState":{"ResourceType":"EntityState","Id":77,"Name":"Done"}},{"ResourceType":"UserStory","Id":213596,"Name":"Insurance Membership Lookup Endpoint","Description":"<!--markdown-->## WHY\nCustomer care operators need to look up insurance policy information for users. Backend must provide a simple endpoint to query memberships by consumer_id for console lookup.\n\n## WHAT\nCreate new REST controller endpoint to retrieve insurance Allianz memberships for a specific consumer.\n\n**Implemented:**\n- Query insurance_allianz_membership by consumer_id\n- Return ALL memberships (ACTIVE + CANCELLED)\n- Paginated response with standard pagination pattern\n- Include policy details in response\n\n---\n\n## API Design\n\n### Endpoint\n```\nGET /v1/insurance_allianz_memberships?consumer_id={uuid}&starting_after={uuid}&limit={int}\n```\n\n### Query Parameters\n\n| Parameter | Type | Required | Default | Description |\n|-----------|------|----------|---------|-------------|\n| `consumer_id` | UUID | Optional | - | Filter by consumer UUID |\n| `starting_after` | UUID | Optional | - | Pagination cursor (membership UID) |\n| `limit` | Integer | Optional | 10 | Page size (number of results) |\n\n### Request Example\n```http\nGET /v1/insurance_allianz_memberships?consumer_id=d375baac-8e36-4c36-8c62-c5dd5cb985fe&limit=10\n```\n\n### Response Example\n```json\n{\n  \"data\": [\n    {\n      \"id\": \"019ae96b-5224-79cd-8b4b-ccb3c2bb07c8\",\n      \"subscription_id\": \"019ae96b-5224-79cd-8b4b-ccb3c2bb07c8\",\n      \"consumer_id\": \"d375baac-8e36-4c36-8c62-c5dd5cb985fe\",\n      \"card_number\": \"S2T6D8E4\",\n      \"tracking_code\": \"AWP2025BASE\",\n      \"plan_level\": 10,\n      \"status\": \"CANCELLED\",\n      \"activation_date\": \"2026-02-01T00:00:00Z\",\n      \"cancellation_date\": \"2026-02-19T18:10:00Z\",\n      \"policies\": [\n        {\n          \"number\": \"IY410005779\",\n          \"premium\": 0.32\n        }\n      ]\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": \"019ae96b-1234-79cd-8b4b-ccb3c2bb07c9\",\n      \"subscription_id\": \"019ae96b-1234-79cd-8b4b-ccb3c2bb07c9\",\n      \"consumer_id\": \"d375baac-8e36-4c36-8c62-c5dd5cb985fe\",\n      \"card_number\": \"S2T6D8E4\",\n      \"tracking_code\": \"AWP2025BASE\",\n      \"plan_level\": 10,\n      \"status\": \"ACTIVE\",\n      \"activation_date\": \"2026-02-20T00:00:00Z\",\n      \"cancellation_date\": null,\n      \"policies\": [\n        {\n          \"number\": \"IY410005780\",\n          \"premium\": 0.32\n        }\n      ]\n    }\n  ],\n  \"has_more\": false\n}\n```","CreateDate":"\/Date(1771625153000+0100)\/","Owner":{"ResourceType":"GeneralUser","Id":978,"Login":"aldo.lushkja@satispay.com"},"Project":{"ResourceType":"Project","Id":186131,"Name":"[IT-B] Satispay Plus"},"EntityState":{"ResourceType":"EntityState","Id":77,"Name":"Done"}},{"ResourceType":"UserStory","Id":213594,"Name":"Pre-signed Download URLs for Partner Export Files","Description":"<!--markdown-->## WHY\nPartner export files (insurance Allianz membership CSVs) are stored in S3 and tracked in the `partner_export` table. We need a secure way to download these files without AWS credentials or permanent public URLs.\n\n## WHAT\nEnhanced the existing partner export load endpoint to optionally include time-limited download URLs:\n\n- **Endpoint**: `GET /v1/partner_exports/{id}?include_presigned_url=true`\n- **Input**: Partner export record ID + optional query parameter\n- **Output**: Standard partner export response with optional pre-signed S3 URL field\n- **URL Validity**: 1 hour\n- **Behavior**:\n  - Returns `presigned_url: null` if parameter is `false` or omitted\n  - Returns `presigned_url: null` if `s3_key` is not present (no validation errors)\n  - Returns `presigned_url: \"https://...\"` if parameter is `true` and `s3_key` exists","CreateDate":"\/Date(1771620849000+0100)\/","Owner":{"ResourceType":"GeneralUser","Id":978,"Login":"aldo.lushkja@satispay.com"},"Project":{"ResourceType":"Project","Id":186131,"Name":"[IT-B] Satispay Plus"},"EntityState":{"ResourceType":"EntityState","Id":77,"Name":"Done"}}]}
