2026-03-07 00:36:21.751 [boundedElastic-1] DEBUG c.i.m.t.service.TargetProcessService - Response status=200 body={"Items":[{"ResourceType":"UserStory","Id":205998,"Name":"[consumer_loyalty][prod] Update multiplier for business premium merchants","Description":"<!--markdown--># WHY\n\nWe need to migrate 14 merchants to the new Business Premium loyalty campaign structure.\n\n# WHAT\n\nUsing **Postman Collection Runner** with the following files:                                                                                                                         \n1. `business-premium-migration.csv` - Contains merchant_id and amount columns                                                                                                        \n2. `curl.sh` - API request template with variable placeholders\n\n```bash\ncurl --location 'https://internal-admin-api.satispay.aws/consumer/consumer-loyalty/v1/campaigns/' \\\n--header 'Content-Type: application/json' \\\n--header 'User-Agent: insomnia/11.2.0' \\\n--data '{\n    \"entity_id\": \"{{merchant_id}}\",\n    \"entity_type\": \"MERCHANT\",\n    \"start_date\": \"2025-12-11T14:59:00.000Z\",\n    \"end_date\": \"2026-12-11T22:59:59.000Z\",\n    \"value\": {{amount}}\n}'\n```","CreateDate":"\/Date(1765439323000+0100)\/","Owner":{"ResourceType":"GeneralUser","Id":978,"Login":"aldo.lushkja@satispay.com"},"Project":{"ResourceType":"Project","Id":140686,"Name":"[IT] Consumer Data Migration"},"EntityState":{"ResourceType":"EntityState","Id":465,"Name":"Done"}},{"ResourceType":"UserStory","Id":205319,"Name":"[consumer_loyalty][prod] GIFT 100K points to users","Description":"<!--markdown--># WHY\n\nIn order to reward our 100 top users.\n\n# WHAT\n\nLaunch the request using Postman Runner and using the CSV attached as source of the data:\n\n```shell\ncurl --request POST \\\n  --url https://internal-admin-api.satispay.aws/consumer/consumer-loyalty/v1/balance_movements \\\n  --header 'Content-Type: application/json' \\\n  --header 'Idempotency-Key: {{idempotencyKey}}' \\\n  --data '{\n    \"consumer_id\": \"{{consumerId}}\",\n    \"total_points\":100000\n}'\n```\n\n[loyalty-gift-top-100.csv](https://satispay.tpondemand.com/Attachment.aspx?AttachmentID=50185)","CreateDate":"\/Date(1764848786000+0100)\/","Owner":{"ResourceType":"GeneralUser","Id":978,"Login":"aldo.lushkja@satispay.com"},"Project":{"ResourceType":"Project","Id":140686,"Name":"[IT] Consumer Data Migration"},"EntityState":{"ResourceType":"EntityState","Id":465,"Name":"Done"}},{"ResourceType":"UserStory","Id":204447,"Name":"CashPooling Cleanup old resources","Description":"<!--markdown--># WHY \n\nThe project has already implement a cash_pooling mechanism a little bit different from the library one.\n\nTo guarantee a correct behaviour of the new implementation and to cleanup duplicate resources.\n\n# WHAT\n\nCleanup old integrations with cash_pooling services. Cleanup previous old package \"cash_pooling\" from service, controllers, job and fix implementations broken. We want a clear situation when no overlap exists between library and old implementations.","CreateDate":"\/Date(1764320292000+0100)\/","Owner":{"ResourceType":"GeneralUser","Id":978,"Login":"aldo.lushkja@satispay.com"},"Project":{"ResourceType":"Project","Id":8884,"Name":"[IT-B] Promo"},"EntityState":{"ResourceType":"EntityState","Id":77,"Name":"Done"}},{"ResourceType":"UserStory","Id":204253,"Name":"CashPooling Init Migration","Description":"<!--markdown-->__WHY__\n\nBecause we can't do it by ourselves. \ncash_pooling table has now some fields which are going to remain empty. \nPreviously those columns were constraint to be NOT NULL, now we don't need this constraint anymore\n\n\n__WHAT__\nIn both `staging` and `prod` ask for those migrations:\n\nALTER TABLE cash_pooling ALTER COLUMN currency DROP NOT NULL;\nALTER TABLE cash_pooling ALTER COLUMN start_date DROP NOT NULL;\nALTER TABLE cash_pooling ALTER COLUMN end_date DROP NOT NULL;\nALTER TABLE cash_pooling ALTER COLUMN end_date_order_unique DROP NOT NULL;\n\n\n","CreateDate":"\/Date(1764238247000+0100)\/","Owner":{"ResourceType":"GeneralUser","Id":978,"Login":"aldo.lushkja@satispay.com"},"Project":{"ResourceType":"Project","Id":8884,"Name":"[IT-B] Promo"},"EntityState":{"ResourceType":"EntityState","Id":77,"Name":"Done"}},{"ResourceType":"UserStory","Id":204251,"Name":"CashPooling Job","Description":"<!--markdown--># WHY\n\nWe have to launch the operation automatically every night with a scheduled frequency.\n\n# WHAT\n\nCreate a new job to handle scheduling of the operation nightly every day at 02:30 UTC.\n\n```java\n@Component\n@ConditionalOnProperty(\"jobs.enabled\")\npublic class CashPoolingJob {\n\n    private final JobService jobService;\n    private final CashPoolingService cashPoolingService;\n    private final CashPoolingMonitoringService monitoringService;\n\n    public CashPoolingJob(JobService jobService,\n                          CashPoolingService cashPoolingService,\n                          CashPoolingMonitoringService monitoringService) {\n        this.jobService = jobService;\n        this.cashPoolingService = cashPoolingService;\n        this.monitoringService = monitoringService;\n    }\n\n    @Scheduled(cron = \"${job.promo.cash_pooling.cron}\")\n    public void execute() {\n        String previousDay = DateKeyService.getPreviousDay();\n        jobService.run(\n                ConfigurationKeyEnum.OPERATION_CASH_POOLING_JOB_ENABLED.name(),\n                JobEnum.CASH_POOLING_JOB.name(),\n                () -> startCashPoolingJob(previousDay)\n        );\n    }\n\n    void startCashPoolingJob(String dateKey) {\n        monitoringService.executeWithMonitoring(dateKey, () -> cashPoolingService.execute(dateKey));\n    }\n}\n```\n\nAdd the new property into file **jobs.properties** inside properties/default directory\n\n`job.promo.cash_pooling.cron=0 30 2 * * *`\n\nAdd the new property also in `bck_application_properties` project for all environments.\n","CreateDate":"\/Date(1764238214000+0100)\/","Owner":{"ResourceType":"GeneralUser","Id":978,"Login":"aldo.lushkja@satispay.com"},"Project":{"ResourceType":"Project","Id":8884,"Name":"[IT-B] Promo"},"EntityState":{"ResourceType":"EntityState","Id":77,"Name":"Done"}},{"ResourceType":"UserStory","Id":204249,"Name":"CashPooling Controllers","Description":"<!--markdown--># WHY\n\nGive the ability to perform action manually and retrieve info for the `cash_pooling` operation.\n\n# WHAT\n\nCreate new apis to achieve this functionalities:\n- execute operation manually for a given date_key\n- retrieve record info for a given date_key\n- perform amount calculation for a given date_key\n\nCreate a Controller class like this:\n\n```java\n@Path(\"/v1/cash_pooling\")\n@Produces(CONTENT_TYPE_JSON)\npublic class CashPoolingController extends SatispayAbstractController {\n\n    private final CashPoolingExecuteDelegate executeDelegate;\n    private final CashPoolingLoadDelegate loadDelegate;\n\n    @Autowired\n    public CashPoolingController(CashPoolingExecuteDelegate executeDelegate,\n                                 CashPoolingLoadDelegate loadDelegate) {\n        this.executeDelegate = executeDelegate;\n        this.loadDelegate = loadDelegate;\n    }\n\n    @GET\n    public CashPoolingResponseBean getByDateKey(@QueryParam(\"date_key\") String dateKey){\n        return loadDelegate.findByDateKey(dateKey);\n    }\n\n    @GET\n    @Path(\"/amount\")\n    public Long amount(@QueryParam(\"date_key\") String dateKey){\n        return executeDelegate.computeAmount(dateKey);\n    }\n\n    @POST\n    @Path(\"/execute\")\n    public void executeCashPooling(@QueryParam(\"date_key\") String dateKey){\n        executeDelegate.startCashPooling(dateKey);\n    }\n}\n```\n\nCreate required delegates for execution and load operations:\n\n- ExecuteDelegate\n\n```java\n@Component\npublic class CashPoolingExecuteDelegate {\n\n    private final CashPoolingService cashPoolingService;\n    private final CashPoolingMonitoringService monitoringService;\n    private final RebalanceAmountProvider rebalanceAmountProvider;\n\n    CashPoolingExecuteDelegate(CashPoolingService cashPoolingService,\n                               CashPoolingMonitoringService monitoringService,\n                               RebalanceAmountProvider rebalanceAmountProvider) {\n        this.cashPoolingService = cashPoolingService;\n        this.monitoringService = monitoringService;\n        this.rebalanceAmountProvider = rebalanceAmountProvider;\n    }\n\n    public void startCashPooling(String dateKey){\n        try {\n            CashPoolingResult result = Optional.ofNullable(dateKey)\n                    .map(key -> monitoringService.executeWithMonitoring(key, () -> cashPoolingService.execute(key)))\n                    .orElseThrow(() -> new ControllerException(ErrorResponseEnum.INTERNAL_SERVER_ERROR));\n\n            if (!result.successful()) {\n                throw new ControllerException(ErrorResponseEnum.BAD_REQUEST, result.error());\n            }\n        } catch (ControllerException e) {\n            throw e;\n        } catch (Exception e) {\n            throw new ControllerException(ErrorResponseEnum.INTERNAL_SERVER_ERROR, e.getMessage());\n        }\n    }\n\n    public Long computeAmount(String dateKey) {\n        if(DateKeyService.isDateKeyInvalid(dateKey)){\n            throw new ControllerException(ErrorResponseEnum.BAD_REQUEST, \"date key is not a valid date key\");\n        }\n        return rebalanceAmountProvider.computeRebalanceAmount(dateKey);\n    }\n}\n```\n\n- LoadDelegate\n\n```java\n@Component\npublic class CashPoolingLoadDelegate {\n\n    private final CashPoolingRepository cashPoolingRepository;\n    private final CashPoolingResponseConverter toResponseConverter;\n\n    public CashPoolingLoadDelegate(CashPoolingRepository cashPoolingRepository,\n                                  CashPoolingResponseConverter toResponseConverter) {\n        this.cashPoolingRepository = cashPoolingRepository;\n        this.toResponseConverter = toResponseConverter;\n    }\n\n    public CashPoolingResponseBean findByDateKey(String dateKey) {\n        return cashPoolingRepository.findByDateKey(dateKey)\n                .map(toResponseConverter::convert)\n                .orElseThrow(() -> new ControllerException(ErrorResponseEnum.RESOURCE_NOT_FOUND));\n    }\n\n}\n```\n\nAlso required beans and converters can be found here: https://github.com/satispay-tech/bck_consumer_reward/tree/main/src/main/java/com/satispay/consumer_reward/controller/cash_pooling","CreateDate":"\/Date(1764238022000+0100)\/","Owner":{"ResourceType":"GeneralUser","Id":978,"Login":"aldo.lushkja@satispay.com"},"Project":{"ResourceType":"Project","Id":8884,"Name":"[IT-B] Promo"},"EntityState":{"ResourceType":"EntityState","Id":77,"Name":"Done"}},{"ResourceType":"UserStory","Id":204248,"Name":"CashPooling Service","Description":"<!--markdown--># WHY\n\nIn order to execute the operation the service class must be created. This class connects `CashPoolingConfig`, `RebalanceAmountProvider` and `CashPoolingRepository` in the same place.\n\n\n# WHAT\n\nCreate the @Bean for the CashPoolingService provided by the library inside **CashPoolingConfiguration** class.\n\n```java\n    @Bean\n    CashPoolingService cashPoolingService(CashPoolingConfig cashPoolingConfig,\n                                          CashPoolingRepository cashPoolingRepository,\n                                          RebalanceAmountProvider rebalanceAmountProvider) {\n        return CashPoolingService.builder()\n                .config(cashPoolingConfig)\n                .repository(cashPoolingRepository)\n                .amountProvider(rebalanceAmountProvider)\n                .build();\n    }\n```\n\nEnrich the library implementation with CloudWatch Monitoring for this events :\n- JOB_STARTED (check for missing launchs)\n- JOB_ERROR (check for operation errors clearing_house/transaction/mms or database)\n- JOB_DURATION_MS (check performance degradation, query lookup, ext-api call)\n\nAn implementation here:\n\n```java\n@Service\npublic class CashPoolingMonitoringService {\n\n    private static final Logger logger = LoggerFactory.getLogger(CashPoolingMonitoringService.class);\n    private static final String DATE_KEY_DIMENSION_NAME = \"dateKey\";\n    private static final String DURATION_MS_DIMENSION_NAME = \"durationMs\";\n    private static final String ERROR_DIMENSION_NAME = \"error\";\n    private static final String THRESHOLD_MS_DIMENSION_NAME = \"thresholdMs\";\n\n    private final CloudWatchInternalService cloudWatchInternalService;\n    private final ConfigurationService configurationService;\n\n    public CashPoolingMonitoringService(CloudWatchInternalService cloudWatchInternalService,\n                                       ConfigurationService configurationService) {\n        this.cloudWatchInternalService = cloudWatchInternalService;\n        this.configurationService = configurationService;\n    }\n\n    public CashPoolingResult executeWithMonitoring(String dateKey, Supplier<CashPoolingResult> operation) {\n        long startTime = System.currentTimeMillis();\n\n        logger.info(\"CASH_POOLING_STARTED - dateKey: {}\", dateKey);\n        cloudWatchInternalService.sendEventWithDimensions(\n            CloudWatchEventEnum.CASH_POOLING_JOB_STARTED,\n            Map.of(DATE_KEY_DIMENSION_NAME, dateKey)\n        );\n\n        try {\n            CashPoolingResult result = operation.get();\n            long duration = System.currentTimeMillis() - startTime;\n\n            if (!result.successful()) {\n                handleFailure(dateKey, result.error(), duration);\n            } else {\n                handleSuccess(dateKey, duration);\n            }\n\n            return result;\n        } catch (Exception e) {\n            long duration = System.currentTimeMillis() - startTime;\n            handleException(dateKey, e, duration);\n            throw e;\n        }\n    }\n\n    private void handleSuccess(String dateKey, long duration) {\n        logger.info(\"CASH_POOLING_COMPLETED - dateKey: {} | duration: {}ms\", dateKey, duration);\n        cloudWatchInternalService.sendEventWithDimensions(\n            CloudWatchEventEnum.CASH_POOLING_JOB_COMPLETED,\n            Map.of(\n                DATE_KEY_DIMENSION_NAME, dateKey,\n                DURATION_MS_DIMENSION_NAME, String.valueOf(duration)\n            )\n        );\n\n        checkDurationThreshold(dateKey, duration);\n    }\n\n    private void handleFailure(String dateKey, String error, long duration) {\n        logger.error(\"CASH_POOLING_FAILED - dateKey: {} | error: {} | duration: {}ms\",\n            dateKey, error, duration);\n        cloudWatchInternalService.sendEventWithDimensions(\n            CloudWatchEventEnum.CASH_POOLING_JOB_FAILED,\n            Map.of(\n                DATE_KEY_DIMENSION_NAME, dateKey,\n                ERROR_DIMENSION_NAME, error != null ? error : \"Unknown\",\n                DURATION_MS_DIMENSION_NAME, String.valueOf(duration)\n            )\n        );\n    }\n\n    private void handleException(String dateKey, Exception e, long duration) {\n        logger.error(\"CASH_POOLING_FAILED - dateKey: {} | error: {} | duration: {}ms\",\n            dateKey, e.getMessage(), duration, e);\n        cloudWatchInternalService.sendEventWithDimensions(\n            CloudWatchEventEnum.CASH_POOLING_JOB_FAILED,\n            Map.of(\n                DATE_KEY_DIMENSION_NAME, dateKey,\n                ERROR_DIMENSION_NAME, e.getMessage() != null ? e.getMessage() : e.getClass().getSimpleName(),\n                DURATION_MS_DIMENSION_NAME, String.valueOf(duration)\n            )\n        );\n    }\n\n    private void checkDurationThreshold(String dateKey, long duration) {\n        long thresholdMs = configurationService.getLong(ConfigurationKeyEnum.OPERATION_CASH_POOLING_DURATION_THRESHOLD_MS.name());\n        if (duration > thresholdMs) {\n            logger.warn(\"CASH_POOLING_DURATION_EXCEEDS_THRESHOLD - dateKey: {} | duration: {}ms | threshold: {}ms\",\n                dateKey, duration, thresholdMs);\n            cloudWatchInternalService.sendEventWithDimensions(\n                CloudWatchEventEnum.CASH_POOLING_JOB_DURATION_EXCEEDS_THRESHOLD,\n                Map.of(\n                    DATE_KEY_DIMENSION_NAME, dateKey,\n                    DURATION_MS_DIMENSION_NAME, String.valueOf(duration),\n                    THRESHOLD_MS_DIMENSION_NAME, String.valueOf(thresholdMs)\n                )\n            );\n        }\n    }\n}\n```","CreateDate":"\/Date(1764238016000+0100)\/","Owner":{"ResourceType":"GeneralUser","Id":978,"Login":"aldo.lushkja@satispay.com"},"Project":{"ResourceType":"Project","Id":8884,"Name":"[IT-B] Promo"},"EntityState":{"ResourceType":"EntityState","Id":77,"Name":"Done"}},{"ResourceType":"UserStory","Id":204247,"Name":"CashPooling Amount Provider","Description":"<!--markdown--># WHY\n\nWe must implement library interface ```RebalanceAmountProvider``` in order to perform calculations of the total amount of money to transfer for a specific date.\n\n# WHAT\n\nThe query to implement is this:\n\n```sql\nref_date = '2025-11-01'\nref_date_tomorrow = ref_date + 1 day\nselect sum(r.amount_unit) from reward r where r.status = 'DONE' and r.payment_date between @ref_date and @ref_date_tomorrow;\n```\n\nCreate a new @Component bean like this:\n\n```java\n@Component\npublic class PromoRebalanceAmountProvider implements RebalanceAmountProvider {\n\n    private static final Logger logger = LoggerFactory.getLogger(PromoRebalanceAmountProvider.class);\n    private static final DateTimeFormatter formatter = DateTimeFormatter.ofPattern(\"yyyyMMdd\");\n\n    private final RewardCrudService rewardCrudService;\n\n    public RewardRebalanceAmountProvider(RewardCrudService rewardCrudService) {\n        this.rewardCrudService = rewardCrudService;\n    }\n\n    @Override\n    public Long computeRebalanceAmount(String dateKey) {\n\n        // Parse the dateKey in format yyyyMMdd (e.g., \"20251021\")\n        LocalDate targetDate = LocalDate.parse(dateKey, formatter);\n\n        // Create start and end dates for the day\n        Date startDate = Date.from(targetDate.atStartOfDay(ZoneId.systemDefault()).toInstant());\n        Date endDate = Date.from(targetDate.plusDays(1).atStartOfDay(ZoneId.systemDefault()).toInstant());\n\n        // Load all rewards in DONE status for the given date\n        List<RewardBean> doneRewards = rewardCrudService.loadByStatusAndDate(\n                RewardStatusEnum.DONE,\n                startDate,\n                endDate\n        );\n\n        // Sum up all the reward amounts\n        long amount = doneRewards.stream()\n                .mapToLong(RewardBean::amountUnit)\n                .sum();\n        logger.info(\"Amount of DONE rewards {} for dateKey {} \", amount, dateKey);\n        return amount;\n    }\n```\n\nAlso add this class as a bean inside the **CashPoolingConfiguration.java** class:\n\n```java\n    @Bean\n    public RebalanceAmountProvider rebalanceAmountProvider(RewardCrudService rewardCrudService) {\n        return new PromoRebalanceAmountProvider(rewardCrudService);\n    }\n```","CreateDate":"\/Date(1764238005000+0100)\/","Owner":{"ResourceType":"GeneralUser","Id":978,"Login":"aldo.lushkja@satispay.com"},"Project":{"ResourceType":"Project","Id":8884,"Name":"[IT-B] Promo"},"EntityState":{"ResourceType":"EntityState","Id":77,"Name":"Done"}},{"ResourceType":"UserStory","Id":204246,"Name":"CashPooling Persistence","Description":"<!--markdown--># WHY\n\nWe must persist new records inside the database.\n\n# WHAT\n\nCreate a new ```mapper.xml``` for the ```cash_pooling``` table because we choose to reuse the existing table. \n\n```xml\n<?xml version=\"1.0\" encoding=\"UTF-8\" ?>\n<!DOCTYPE mapper\n        PUBLIC \"-//mybatis.org//DTD Mapper 3.0//EN\"\n        \"http://mybatis.org/dtd/mybatis-3-mapper.dtd\">\n<mapper namespace=\"com.satispay.cash_pooling.persistence.postgresql.mapper.CashPoolingMapper\">\n\n    <resultMap id=\"CashPoolingRecordResultMap\" type=\"com.satispay.cash_pooling.persistence.postgresql.model.CashPoolingRecord\">\n        <constructor>\n            <idArg column=\"uid\" javaType=\"UUID\" jdbcType=\"OTHER\" typeHandler=\"com.satispay.cash_pooling.persistence.postgresql.handler.UUIDTypeHandler\"/>\n            <arg column=\"date_key\" javaType=\"String\" jdbcType=\"VARCHAR\"/>\n            <arg column=\"amount_unit\" javaType=\"Long\" jdbcType=\"BIGINT\"/>\n            <arg column=\"status\" javaType=\"com.satispay.cash_pooling.persistence.postgresql.model.CashPoolingStatus\" jdbcType=\"VARCHAR\" typeHandler=\"com.satispay.cash_pooling.persistence.postgresql.handler.CashPoolingStatusTypeHandler\"/>\n            <arg column=\"clearing_house_sdd_uid\" javaType=\"UUID\" jdbcType=\"OTHER\" typeHandler=\"com.satispay.cash_pooling.persistence.postgresql.handler.UUIDTypeHandler\"/>\n            <arg column=\"clearing_house_idempotent_token\" javaType=\"UUID\" jdbcType=\"OTHER\" typeHandler=\"com.satispay.cash_pooling.persistence.postgresql.handler.UUIDTypeHandler\"/>\n            <arg column=\"transaction_payment_uid\" javaType=\"UUID\" jdbcType=\"OTHER\" typeHandler=\"com.satispay.cash_pooling.persistence.postgresql.handler.UUIDTypeHandler\"/>\n            <arg column=\"transaction_idempotent_token\" javaType=\"UUID\" jdbcType=\"OTHER\" typeHandler=\"com.satispay.cash_pooling.persistence.postgresql.handler.UUIDTypeHandler\"/>\n            <arg column=\"ledger_entry_uid\" javaType=\"UUID\" jdbcType=\"OTHER\" typeHandler=\"com.satispay.cash_pooling.persistence.postgresql.handler.UUIDTypeHandler\"/>\n            <arg column=\"ledger_entry_idempotent_token\" javaType=\"UUID\" jdbcType=\"OTHER\" typeHandler=\"com.satispay.cash_pooling.persistence.postgresql.handler.UUIDTypeHandler\"/>\n            <arg column=\"insert_date\" javaType=\"java.util.Date\" jdbcType=\"TIMESTAMP\"/>\n            <arg column=\"update_date\" javaType=\"java.util.Date\" jdbcType=\"TIMESTAMP\"/>\n            <arg column=\"order_unique\" javaType=\"Long\" jdbcType=\"BIGINT\"/>\n            <arg column=\"version\" javaType=\"Long\" jdbcType=\"BIGINT\"/>\n        </constructor>\n    </resultMap>\n\n    <select id=\"findByDateKey\" resultMap=\"CashPoolingRecordResultMap\">\n        SELECT *\n        FROM cash_pooling\n        WHERE date_key = #{dateKey}\n    </select>\n\n    <select id=\"findById\" resultMap=\"CashPoolingRecordResultMap\">\n        SELECT *\n        FROM cash_pooling\n        WHERE uid = #{uid}::uuid\n    </select>\n\n    <insert id=\"insert\">\n        INSERT INTO cash_pooling (\n            uid, date_key, amount_unit, status,\n            clearing_house_sdd_uid, clearing_house_idempotent_token,\n            transaction_payment_uid, transaction_idempotent_token,\n            ledger_entry_uid, ledger_entry_idempotent_token,\n            order_unique, version\n        ) VALUES (\n            #{uid, jdbcType=OTHER},\n            #{dateKey, jdbcType=VARCHAR},\n            #{amountUnit, jdbcType=BIGINT},\n            #{status, jdbcType=VARCHAR, typeHandler=com.satispay.cash_pooling.persistence.postgresql.handler.CashPoolingStatusTypeHandler},\n            #{clearingHouseSddUid, jdbcType=OTHER},\n            #{clearingHouseIdempotentToken, jdbcType=OTHER},\n            #{transactionPaymentUid, jdbcType=OTHER},\n            #{transactionIdempotentToken, jdbcType=OTHER},\n            #{ledgerEntryUid, jdbcType=OTHER},\n            #{ledgerEntryIdempotentToken, jdbcType=OTHER},\n            #{orderUnique, jdbcType=BIGINT},\n            COALESCE(#{version, jdbcType=BIGINT}, 0)\n        )\n    </insert>\n\n    <update id=\"update\">\n        UPDATE cash_pooling\n        SET amount_unit = #{amountUnit, jdbcType=BIGINT},\n            status = #{status, jdbcType=VARCHAR, typeHandler=com.satispay.cash_pooling.persistence.postgresql.handler.CashPoolingStatusTypeHandler},\n            clearing_house_sdd_uid = #{clearingHouseSddUid, jdbcType=OTHER},\n            clearing_house_idempotent_token = #{clearingHouseIdempotentToken, jdbcType=OTHER},\n            transaction_payment_uid = #{transactionPaymentUid, jdbcType=OTHER},\n            transaction_idempotent_token = #{transactionIdempotentToken, jdbcType=OTHER},\n            ledger_entry_uid = #{ledgerEntryUid, jdbcType=OTHER},\n            ledger_entry_idempotent_token = #{ledgerEntryIdempotentToken, jdbcType=OTHER},\n            update_date = NOW(),\n            version = version + 1\n        WHERE date_key = #{dateKey}\n          AND version = #{version, jdbcType=BIGINT}\n    </update>\n\n    <update id=\"updateSkipNull\">\n        UPDATE cash_pooling\n        <set>\n            <if test=\"amountUnit != null\">\n                amount_unit = #{amountUnit, jdbcType=BIGINT},\n            </if>\n            <if test=\"status != null\">\n                status = #{status, jdbcType=VARCHAR, typeHandler=com.satispay.cash_pooling.persistence.postgresql.handler.CashPoolingStatusTypeHandler},\n            </if>\n            <if test=\"clearingHouseSddUid != null\">\n                clearing_house_sdd_uid = #{clearingHouseSddUid, jdbcType=OTHER},\n            </if>\n            <if test=\"clearingHouseIdempotentToken != null\">\n                clearing_house_idempotent_token = #{clearingHouseIdempotentToken, jdbcType=OTHER},\n            </if>\n            <if test=\"transactionPaymentUid != null\">\n                transaction_payment_uid = #{transactionPaymentUid, jdbcType=OTHER},\n            </if>\n            <if test=\"transactionIdempotentToken != null\">\n                transaction_idempotent_token = #{transactionIdempotentToken, jdbcType=OTHER},\n            </if>\n            <if test=\"ledgerEntryUid != null\">\n                ledger_entry_uid = #{ledgerEntryUid, jdbcType=OTHER},\n            </if>\n            <if test=\"ledgerEntryIdempotentToken != null\">\n                ledger_entry_idempotent_token = #{ledgerEntryIdempotentToken, jdbcType=OTHER},\n            </if>\n            update_date = NOW(),\n            version = version + 1\n        </set>\n        WHERE date_key = #{dateKey}\n          AND version = #{version, jdbcType=BIGINT}\n    </update>\n\n    <delete id=\"delete\">\n        DELETE FROM cash_pooling\n        WHERE uid = #{uid}::uuid\n    </delete>\n\n</mapper>\n```\n\nBy writing the mapper inside the right directory\n\nProvide a migration creating new columns for the existing table.\n\n```sql\nALTER TABLE cash_pooling ADD column ...\n```\n\nAdd dao implementation the configuration class.\n\n```java\n@Bean\nCashPoolingRepository cashPoolingRepository(SqlSessionFactory sqlSessionFactory){\n\treturn new MyBatisCashPoolingRepository(sqlSessionFactory);\n}\n```\n","CreateDate":"\/Date(1764237993000+0100)\/","Owner":{"ResourceType":"GeneralUser","Id":978,"Login":"aldo.lushkja@satispay.com"},"Project":{"ResourceType":"Project","Id":8884,"Name":"[IT-B] Promo"},"EntityState":{"ResourceType":"EntityState","Id":77,"Name":"Done"}},{"ResourceType":"UserStory","Id":204245,"Name":"CashPooling Configuration","Description":"<!--markdown--># WHY\n\nWe need to import the library for the cash_pooling operation.\n\nWe must configure required accounts needed for the operation to work.\n\n# WHAT\n\nImport the library inside you project in the **build.gradle** file:\n\n```bash\n    def satispayCashPoolingVersion = '1.0.4'\n\n     ....\n\n      implementation(\"com.satispay:cash_pooling:${satispayCashPoolingVersion}\"){\n        exclude group: \"com.satispay.tools\"\n        exclude group: 'ch.qos.logback'\n        exclude group: 'org.slf4j'\n    }\n```\n\nCreate a new class CashPoolingConfigurations with @Configuration annotation.\n\n```java\n@Configuration\npublic class CashPoolingConfiguration {\n\n    private final AppConfiguration appConfiguration;\n    private final ConfigurationService configurationService;\n\n    public CashPoolingConfiguration(AppConfiguration appConfiguration, ConfigurationService configurationService) {\n        this.appConfiguration = appConfiguration;\n        this.configurationService = configurationService;\n    }\n\n    private SdkConfiguration sdkConfiguration() {\n        return SdkConfiguration.builder()\n                .withClientConfiguration(appConfiguration.getClientConfiguration())\n                .withServiceConfiguration(appConfiguration.serviceConfiguration())\n                .build();\n    }\n\n    @Bean\n    public CashPoolingConfig cashPoolingConfig() {\n        return CashPoolingConfig.builder()\n                .accountId(configurationService.getUUID(ConfigurationKeyEnum.OPERATION_CASH_POOLING_ACCOUNT_ID.name()))\n                .ibanId(configurationService.getUUID(ConfigurationKeyEnum.OPERATION_CASH_POOLING_IBAN_ID.name()))\n                .mandateId(configurationService.getUUID(ConfigurationKeyEnum.OPERATION_CASH_POOLING_MANDATE_ID.name()))\n                .technicalWalletId(configurationService.getUUID(ConfigurationKeyEnum.OPERATION_CASH_POOLING_TECHNICAL_WALLET_ID.name()))\n                .remittance(configurationService.getString(ConfigurationKeyEnum.OPERATION_CASH_POOLING_REMITTANCE.name()))\n                .ledgerEntryType(configurationService.getString(ConfigurationKeyEnum.OPERATION_CASH_POOLING_LEDGER_ENTRY_TYPE.name()))\n                .sdkConfiguration(sdkConfiguration())\n                .build();\n    }\n}\n```\n\nIn **ConfigureKeyEnum.java** add this new keys:\n\n```java\n    // ==============================\n    //     CASH_POOLING_CONFIGS     =\n    // ==============================\n    OPERATION_CASH_POOLING_JOB_ENABLED(\"false\"),\n    OPERATION_CASH_POOLING_ACCOUNT_ID(\"028caf33-13d2-4914-aaf5-e538a1f9dc50\"), \n    OPERATION_CASH_POOLING_IBAN_ID(\"7aee7402-054b-4a32-bd2e-19a950f9207c\"),\n    OPERATION_CASH_POOLING_MANDATE_ID(\"dd89b225-5df1-4ddc-b0fb-fef29d3d3ef9\"),\n    OPERATION_CASH_POOLING_TECHNICAL_WALLET_ID(null),\n    OPERATION_CASH_POOLING_REMITTANCE(\"Daily Cash Pooling - Promo\"),\n    OPERATION_CASH_POOLING_LEDGER_ENTRY_TYPE(\"PROMO\"),\n    OPERATION_CASH_POOLING_DURATION_THRESHOLD_MS(\"300000\"), // 5 minutes in milliseconds\n```","CreateDate":"\/Date(1764237980000+0100)\/","Owner":{"ResourceType":"GeneralUser","Id":978,"Login":"aldo.lushkja@satispay.com"},"Project":{"ResourceType":"Project","Id":8884,"Name":"[IT-B] Promo"},"EntityState":{"ResourceType":"EntityState","Id":77,"Name":"Done"}},{"ResourceType":"UserStory","Id":203983,"Name":"Bump SDK version to support PROMO ledger entry","Description":"<!--markdown--># WHY\n\nIn order to finalize the CP integration.\n\n# WHAT\n\nBump SDK version to `1.2532.00`","CreateDate":"\/Date(1764080792000+0100)\/","Owner":{"ResourceType":"GeneralUser","Id":978,"Login":"aldo.lushkja@satispay.com"},"Project":{"ResourceType":"Project","Id":197811,"Name":"[IT-B] Cash Pooling Library"},"EntityState":{"ResourceType":"EntityState","Id":77,"Name":"Done"}},{"ResourceType":"UserStory","Id":203848,"Name":"[consumer_reward][prod]Cash Pooling - Add technical wallet","Description":"<!--markdown-->## WHY\n\nExecute the SQL migration to the **consumer_reward** database in order to enable the cash_pooling job.\n\n## WHAT\n\n```sql\nINSERT INTO configuration (key, value, description, version, insert_date)\nVALUES (\n    'OPERATION_CASH_POOLING_TECHNICAL_WALLET_ID',\n    '019ab562-63e6-7395-bb13-4b3cf7aee271',\n    'Technical wallet ID for cash pooling ledger entries',\n    0,\n    timezone('UTC', now())\n)\nON CONFLICT (key) DO UPDATE SET\n    value = EXCLUDED.value,\n    description = EXCLUDED.description,\n    update_date = timezone('UTC', now()),\n    version = configuration.version + 1;\n```\n\nExecute also an instance refresh of  **consumer_reward** service.","CreateDate":"\/Date(1764062293000+0100)\/","Owner":{"ResourceType":"GeneralUser","Id":978,"Login":"aldo.lushkja@satispay.com"},"Project":{"ResourceType":"Project","Id":154072,"Name":"[IT-B] Consumer Reward"},"EntityState":{"ResourceType":"EntityState","Id":77,"Name":"Done"}},{"ResourceType":"UserStory","Id":203758,"Name":"Analyse S+ Insurance Integration","Description":"<!--markdown-->## WHY\nTo strengthen the value proposition of the Satispay Plus base plan, we will introduce the insurance benefit in Q1 2026. This marks the first step in expanding the Plus offering and integrating insurance services that can later be extended to additional plans.\n\n## WHAT\nThe objective of this request is to clarify the implementation details with the insurance provider.\n\nPlease take into account the following principles:\n\nNo opt-in required: consumers will be automatically enrolled in the insurance coverage as part of their Plus subscription.\nIn-app experience: within Satispay, users will only access general and useful information about the insurance service.\nExternal management: all detailed insurance flows, including the full UX, will be handled directly by the insurance provider outside the Satispay app.","CreateDate":"\/Date(1763984239000+0100)\/","Owner":{"ResourceType":"GeneralUser","Id":978,"Login":"aldo.lushkja@satispay.com"},"Project":{"ResourceType":"Project","Id":186131,"Name":"[IT-B] Satispay Plus"},"EntityState":{"ResourceType":"EntityState","Id":77,"Name":"Done"}},{"ResourceType":"UserStory","Id":203502,"Name":"Bump CashPooling lib version to support PROMO ledgerEntryType","Description":"<!--markdown--># WHY\n\nIn order to make the call to MMS fully correct in cash pooling job.\n\n# WHAT\n\nUpgrade CP library to version 1.0.4.","CreateDate":"\/Date(1763653201000+0100)\/","Owner":{"ResourceType":"GeneralUser","Id":978,"Login":"aldo.lushkja@satispay.com"},"Project":{"ResourceType":"Project","Id":154072,"Name":"[IT-B] Consumer Reward"},"EntityState":{"ResourceType":"EntityState","Id":77,"Name":"Done"}},{"ResourceType":"UserStory","Id":203292,"Name":"Implement Outbox for SQS","Description":"<!--markdown--># WHY\n\nIn order to guarantee the **\"at least one\"** delivery behaviour while sending SQS messages and make it transactional with certain operation.\n\nMay happen that we have a domain model update in DB but we have no guarantee that SQS messages is delivered, so a recovery mechanism must be provided to handle this scenario.\n\n# WHAT\n\nImplement what have done with SNS using OutboxService also for SQS. \n\nIf schema table changes needed also provide a migration to insert in flyway directory.","CreateDate":"\/Date(1763544124000+0100)\/","Owner":{"ResourceType":"GeneralUser","Id":978,"Login":"aldo.lushkja@satispay.com"},"Project":{"ResourceType":"Project","Id":186131,"Name":"[IT-B] Satispay Plus"},"EntityState":{"ResourceType":"EntityState","Id":73,"Name":"Open"}},{"ResourceType":"UserStory","Id":202295,"Name":"Make technicalWalletID default to NULL","Description":"<!--markdown-->##  WHY\n\nIn order to deploy changes in PROD for the CP library integration.\n\n## WHAT\n\nUpdate the `OPERATION_CASH_POOLING_TECHNICAL_WALLET_ID` to be **null** as default value. \n\nUpdate library version to version 1.0.3 (handles gracefully the null technical wallet id)","CreateDate":"\/Date(1762780899000+0100)\/","Owner":{"ResourceType":"GeneralUser","Id":978,"Login":"aldo.lushkja@satispay.com"},"Project":{"ResourceType":"Project","Id":154072,"Name":"[IT-B] Consumer Reward"},"EntityState":{"ResourceType":"EntityState","Id":77,"Name":"Done"}},{"ResourceType":"UserStory","Id":202268,"Name":"Make technical_wallet_id optional for configurations and client calls","Description":"<!--markdown-->## WHY\n\nTechnical Wallet ID is an optional configuration.\n\n## WHAT\n\nRemove the required behaviour for configuration value `technical_wallet_id` and make the client aware of possible null value for that configuration.","CreateDate":"\/Date(1762771875000+0100)\/","Owner":{"ResourceType":"GeneralUser","Id":978,"Login":"aldo.lushkja@satispay.com"},"Project":{"ResourceType":"Project","Id":197811,"Name":"[IT-B] Cash Pooling Library"},"EntityState":{"ResourceType":"EntityState","Id":77,"Name":"Done"}},{"ResourceType":"UserStory","Id":201908,"Name":"[consumer_reward][prod]Cash Pooling - Enable Job","Description":"<!--markdown-->## WHY\n\nExecute the SQL migration to the **consumer_reward** database in order to enable the cash_pooling job.\n\n## WHAT\n\n```sql\nINSERT INTO configuration (key, value, description, version, insert_date)\nVALUES (\n    'OPERATION_CASH_POOLING_JOB_ENABLED',\n    'true',\n    'Enable or disable the cash pooling job execution',\n    0,\n    timezone('UTC', now())\n)\nON CONFLICT (key) DO UPDATE SET\n    value = EXCLUDED.value,\n    description = EXCLUDED.description,\n    update_date = timezone('UTC', now()),\n    version = configuration.version + 1;\n```\n\nExecute also an instance refresh of  **consumer_reward** service.","CreateDate":"\/Date(1762421675000+0100)\/","Owner":{"ResourceType":"GeneralUser","Id":978,"Login":"aldo.lushkja@satispay.com"},"Project":{"ResourceType":"Project","Id":154072,"Name":"[IT-B] Consumer Reward"},"EntityState":{"ResourceType":"EntityState","Id":77,"Name":"Done"}},{"ResourceType":"UserStory","Id":201906,"Name":"[consumer_reward][prod]Cash Pooling - Init Config","Description":"<!--markdown-->## WHY\n\nExecute this SQL migration in **consumer_reward** database in order to bootstrap cash_pooling library integration.\n\n## WHAT\n\n```sql\n-- ============================================================================\n-- Cash Pooling Configuration Script\n-- ============================================================================\n-- This script configures the cash pooling operation by setting up all\n-- necessary configuration values in the configuration table.\n--\n-- Usage:\n-- 1. Update the UUID values below with your actual account/IBAN/mandate/wallet IDs\n-- 2. Adjust the remittance and ledger entry type as needed for your service\n-- 3. Execute this script in your PostgreSQL database\n-- 4. Verify: SELECT * FROM configuration WHERE key LIKE 'OPERATION_CASH_POOLING%'\n-- ============================================================================\n\n-- ============================================================================\n-- Main Configuration Values\n-- ============================================================================\n\n-- Enable/Disable Cash Pooling Job\nINSERT INTO configuration (key, value, description, version, insert_date)\nVALUES (\n    'OPERATION_CASH_POOLING_JOB_ENABLED',\n    'false',\n    'Enable or disable the cash pooling job execution',\n    0,\n    timezone('UTC', now())\n)\nON CONFLICT (key) DO UPDATE SET\n    value = EXCLUDED.value,\n    description = EXCLUDED.description,\n    update_date = timezone('UTC', now()),\n    version = configuration.version + 1;\n\n-- ============================================================================\n-- Account Configuration\n-- ============================================================================\n\n-- Account ID - Replace with your actual account UUID\nINSERT INTO configuration (key, value, description, version, insert_date)\nVALUES (\n    'OPERATION_CASH_POOLING_ACCOUNT_ID',\n    'efe81005-eb8a-11e5-95cc-06cb0bb44caf',\n    'Account ID used for cash pooling operations',\n    0,\n    timezone('UTC', now())\n)\nON CONFLICT (key) DO UPDATE SET\n    value = EXCLUDED.value,\n    description = EXCLUDED.description,\n    update_date = timezone('UTC', now()),\n    version = configuration.version + 1;\n\n-- IBAN ID - Replace with your actual IBAN UUID\nINSERT INTO configuration (key, value, description, version, insert_date)\nVALUES (\n    'OPERATION_CASH_POOLING_IBAN_ID',\n    '863984f0-b4c9-484a-a8c0-24855a2b9b47',\n    'IBAN ID for cash pooling account',\n    0,\n    timezone('UTC', now())\n)\nON CONFLICT (key) DO UPDATE SET\n    value = EXCLUDED.value,\n    description = EXCLUDED.description,\n    update_date = timezone('UTC', now()),\n    version = configuration.version + 1;\n\n-- Mandate ID - Replace with your actual mandate UUID\nINSERT INTO configuration (key, value, description, version, insert_date)\nVALUES (\n    'OPERATION_CASH_POOLING_MANDATE_ID',\n    'f3043c9a-de85-4bc2-972e-c5f3e37b541c',\n    'Mandate ID for SEPA Direct Debit in cash pooling',\n    0,\n    timezone('UTC', now())\n)\nON CONFLICT (key) DO UPDATE SET\n    value = EXCLUDED.value,\n    description = EXCLUDED.description,\n    update_date = timezone('UTC', now()),\n    version = configuration.version + 1;\n\n-- ============================================================================\n-- Transaction Configuration\n-- ============================================================================\n\n-- Remittance Information - Customize for your service\nINSERT INTO configuration (key, value, description, version, insert_date)\nVALUES (\n    'OPERATION_CASH_POOLING_REMITTANCE',\n    'Daily Cash Pooling - Reward Rebalance',\n    'Remittance information for cash pooling transactions',\n    0,\n    timezone('UTC', now())\n)\nON CONFLICT (key) DO UPDATE SET\n    value = EXCLUDED.value,\n    description = EXCLUDED.description,\n    update_date = timezone('UTC', now()),\n    version = configuration.version + 1;\n\n-- Ledger Entry Type - Customize for your accounting needs\nINSERT INTO configuration (key, value, description, version, insert_date)\nVALUES (\n    'OPERATION_CASH_POOLING_LEDGER_ENTRY_TYPE',\n    'LOYALTY',\n    'Ledger entry type for cash pooling operations',\n    0,\n    timezone('UTC', now())\n)\nON CONFLICT (key) DO UPDATE SET\n    value = EXCLUDED.value,\n    description = EXCLUDED.description,\n    update_date = timezone('UTC', now()),\n    version = configuration.version + 1;\n\n-- ============================================================================\n-- Performance and Monitoring Configuration\n-- ============================================================================\n\n-- Duration Threshold (in milliseconds)\n-- Default: 300000 ms (5 minutes)\nINSERT INTO configuration (key, value, description, version, insert_date)\nVALUES (\n    'OPERATION_CASH_POOLING_DURATION_THRESHOLD_MS',\n    '300000',\n    'Duration threshold in milliseconds for cash pooling job monitoring',\n    0,\n    timezone('UTC', now())\n)\nON CONFLICT (key) DO UPDATE SET\n    value = EXCLUDED.value,\n    description = EXCLUDED.description,\n    update_date = timezone('UTC', now()),\n    version = configuration.version + 1;\n\n-- ============================================================================\n-- Verification and Summary\n-- ============================================================================\n\nDO $$\nDECLARE\n    config_count INTEGER;\n    enabled_value TEXT;\n    placeholder_count INTEGER := 0;\n    account_id TEXT;\n    iban_id TEXT;\n    mandate_id TEXT;\n    wallet_id TEXT;\nBEGIN\n    -- Count cash pooling configurations\n    SELECT COUNT(*)\n    INTO config_count\n    FROM configuration\n    WHERE key LIKE 'OPERATION_CASH_POOLING%';\n\n    -- Get enabled status\n    SELECT value INTO enabled_value FROM configuration WHERE key = 'OPERATION_CASH_POOLING_JOB_ENABLED';\n\n    -- Fetch configuration values to check for placeholders\n    SELECT value INTO account_id FROM configuration WHERE key = 'OPERATION_CASH_POOLING_ACCOUNT_ID';\n    SELECT value INTO iban_id FROM configuration WHERE key = 'OPERATION_CASH_POOLING_IBAN_ID';\n    SELECT value INTO mandate_id FROM configuration WHERE key = 'OPERATION_CASH_POOLING_MANDATE_ID';\n    SELECT value INTO wallet_id FROM configuration WHERE key = 'OPERATION_CASH_POOLING_TECHNICAL_WALLET_ID';\n\n    -- Check for placeholder values\n    IF account_id LIKE '<%>' THEN placeholder_count := placeholder_count + 1; END IF;\n    IF iban_id LIKE '<%>' THEN placeholder_count := placeholder_count + 1; END IF;\n    IF mandate_id LIKE '<%>' THEN placeholder_count := placeholder_count + 1; END IF;\n    IF wallet_id LIKE '<%>' THEN placeholder_count := placeholder_count + 1; END IF;\n\n    RAISE NOTICE '============================================================================';\n    RAISE NOTICE 'CASH POOLING CONFIGURATION COMPLETED';\n    RAISE NOTICE '============================================================================';\n    RAISE NOTICE 'Total configurations: %', config_count;\n    RAISE NOTICE 'Job enabled: %', enabled_value;\n    RAISE NOTICE '';\n\n    IF placeholder_count > 0 THEN\n        RAISE WARNING '⚠️  WARNING: % placeholder value(s) detected!', placeholder_count;\n        RAISE WARNING '⚠️  Please replace <YOUR_*_UUID_HERE> placeholders with actual UUIDs';\n        RAISE NOTICE '';\n    ELSE\n        RAISE NOTICE '✓ All configuration values set';\n        RAISE NOTICE '';\n    END IF;\n\n    RAISE NOTICE 'Configuration keys created/updated:';\n    RAISE NOTICE '  - OPERATION_CASH_POOLING_JOB_ENABLED: %', enabled_value;\n    RAISE NOTICE '  - OPERATION_CASH_POOLING_ACCOUNT_ID: %', account_id;\n    RAISE NOTICE '  - OPERATION_CASH_POOLING_IBAN_ID: %', iban_id;\n    RAISE NOTICE '  - OPERATION_CASH_POOLING_MANDATE_ID: %', mandate_id;\n    RAISE NOTICE '  - OPERATION_CASH_POOLING_TECHNICAL_WALLET_ID: %', wallet_id;\n    RAISE NOTICE '  - OPERATION_CASH_POOLING_REMITTANCE';\n    RAISE NOTICE '  - OPERATION_CASH_POOLING_LEDGER_ENTRY_TYPE';\n    RAISE NOTICE '  - OPERATION_CASH_POOLING_DURATION_THRESHOLD_MS';\n    RAISE NOTICE '';\n    RAISE NOTICE 'To view all configurations:';\n    RAISE NOTICE '  SELECT * FROM configuration WHERE key LIKE ''OPERATION_CASH_POOLING%%'';';\n    RAISE NOTICE '============================================================================';\nEND $$;\n","CreateDate":"\/Date(1762421513000+0100)\/","Owner":{"ResourceType":"GeneralUser","Id":978,"Login":"aldo.lushkja@satispay.com"},"Project":{"ResourceType":"Project","Id":140686,"Name":"[IT] Consumer Data Migration"},"EntityState":{"ResourceType":"EntityState","Id":465,"Name":"Done"}},{"ResourceType":"UserStory","Id":201905,"Name":"Create dry-run controller","Description":"<!--markdown-->## WHY\n\nIn order to verify if the calculation done is correct can be useful to expose a `/v1/cash_pooling/amount` API that only does the calculation of the cash pooling amount without making the real calls to the external APIs.\n\n## WHAT\n\nExpose a controller like this `/v1/cash_pooling/amount`\n\n- **query-param**: `date_key`\n- **return**: the amount calculated for that given date_key\n\n```java\n@POST\n@Path(\"/amount\")\n public Long amount(@QueryParam(\"date_key\") String dateKey){\n        return loadDelegate.computeAmount(dateKey);\n  }\n```","CreateDate":"\/Date(1762421222000+0100)\/","Owner":{"ResourceType":"GeneralUser","Id":978,"Login":"aldo.lushkja@satispay.com"},"Project":{"ResourceType":"Project","Id":154072,"Name":"[IT-B] Consumer Reward"},"EntityState":{"ResourceType":"EntityState","Id":77,"Name":"Done"}},{"ResourceType":"UserStory","Id":201897,"Name":"Doc refinements","Description":"<!--markdown--># WHY\nHighlight edge cases and requirements for the library.\n\nCheck missing steps needed while integrating with the library.\n\n# WHAT\n\n - Write with RED color the fact that updating the configuration in database for the CashPoolingConfig, to propagate the change to the application an instance refresh is needed.\n- Add MyBatis model in mybatis-postgresql-config.xml\n\n","CreateDate":"\/Date(1762420320000+0100)\/","Owner":{"ResourceType":"GeneralUser","Id":978,"Login":"aldo.lushkja@satispay.com"},"Project":{"ResourceType":"Project","Id":197811,"Name":"[IT-B] Cash Pooling Library"},"EntityState":{"ResourceType":"EntityState","Id":73,"Name":"Open"}},{"ResourceType":"UserStory","Id":201896,"Name":"Handle negative cashpooling amounts","Description":"<!--markdown-->## WHY\n\nTBD\n\n## WHAT\n\nTBD","CreateDate":"\/Date(1762420303000+0100)\/","Owner":{"ResourceType":"GeneralUser","Id":978,"Login":"aldo.lushkja@satispay.com"},"Project":{"ResourceType":"Project","Id":197811,"Name":"[IT-B] Cash Pooling Library"},"EntityState":{"ResourceType":"EntityState","Id":73,"Name":"Open"}},{"ResourceType":"UserStory","Id":201895,"Name":"Fix LedgerEntry ssdUid using the ClearingHouse once","Description":"<!--markdown-->## WHY\n\nLedger Entry call made by the library uses wrongly the **paymentUid** inside the **bankTransfer** object instead of the **clearingHouseUid**\n\n## WHAT\n\n```java\n    private LedgerEntryInternalRequestBean buildLedgerEntryRequest(CashPoolingRecord cashPoolingRecord, CashPoolingConfig config) {\n        return new LedgerEntryInternalRequestBeanBuilder()\n                .withType(config.ledgerEntryType())\n                .withCounterpart(CounterpartInternalRequestBean.builder()\n                        .withId(config.accountId())\n                        .withType(CounterpartTypeEnum.CASH_POOLING)\n                        .build())\n                .withBankTransfer(BankTransferInternalRequestBean.builder()\n                        .withId(cashPoolingRecord.clearingHouseSddUid()) // <-- Updated data\n                        .withType(BankTransferTypeEnum.SDD)\n                        .build())\n                .build();\n    }\n```","CreateDate":"\/Date(1762420112000+0100)\/","Owner":{"ResourceType":"GeneralUser","Id":978,"Login":"aldo.lushkja@satispay.com"},"Project":{"ResourceType":"Project","Id":197811,"Name":"[IT-B] Cash Pooling Library"},"EntityState":{"ResourceType":"EntityState","Id":77,"Name":"Done"}},{"ResourceType":"UserStory","Id":201893,"Name":"Mark record DONE and do not thrown an exception for 0 amount","Description":"<!--markdown-->## WHY\n\nHandle 0 amount cash pooling gracefully. The current implementation marks the record as REQUESTED and throws an exception.\n\n## WHAT\n\nUpdate this peace of code to log in WARN level instead of throwing an exception.\n\n```java\n    Long validateAmount(Long amount) {\n        if (amount <= 0) {\n            throw new CashPoolingException(\"Invalid amount provided: \" + amount); // <-- Update here\n        }\n        return amount;\n    }\n\n```\n\nIn the CashPoolingServiceExecutor::startCashPooling update the logic so when amount == 0 the simply update the record with status DONE.\n\n```java\npublic CashPoolingResult startCashPooling(String dateKey) {\n        if (DateKeyService.isDateKeyInvalid(dateKey)) {\n            throw new CashPoolingException(\"Invalid date key provided: \" + dateKey);\n        }\n        CashPoolingRecord cashPoolingRecord = loadOrCreate(dateKey);\n        if (cashPoolingRecord.status() == CashPoolingStatus.DONE) {\n            return CashPoolingResult.completed();\n        }\n        Long amount = validateAmount(amountProvider.computeRebalanceAmount(dateKey));\n\t// START - Update\n\tif(amount == 0){\n\t\tvar updatedRecord = cashPoolingRecord.toBuilder().withAmount(amount).withStatus(DONE).build();\n\t\tcashPoolingRepository.update(updatedRecord);\n\t\treturn CashPoolingResult.completed();\n\t}\n\t// END - Update\n        processCashPooling(cashPoolingRecord, amount);\n        return CashPoolingResult.completed();\n    }\n```","CreateDate":"\/Date(1762420083000+0100)\/","Owner":{"ResourceType":"GeneralUser","Id":978,"Login":"aldo.lushkja@satispay.com"},"Project":{"ResourceType":"Project","Id":197811,"Name":"[IT-B] Cash Pooling Library"},"EntityState":{"ResourceType":"EntityState","Id":73,"Name":"Open"}},{"ResourceType":"UserStory","Id":201892,"Name":"Avoid calling services when UUID is present","Description":"<!--markdown-->## WHY\n\nIn order to not waste I/O resources when the request for a given service is already completed do not make the call to the service again. No problem is raised because we have the idempotencyKey for each external call, but avoid unncessary calls can improve the resource usage of the library and also free external service for network calls and computation not needed.\n\n## WHAT\n\nMake the create[clearingHouse|payment|ledgerEntry] aware of the fact that when a response is already present for the given service simply return the cash pooling record.\n\nAn example here below:\n\n```java\nprivate CashPoolingRecord createClearingHouseSdd(CashPoolingRecord cashPoolingRecord) {\n        // START - Update\n\tif(cashPoolingRecord.clearingHouseSddUid() != null) {\n            return cashPoolingRecord;\n        }\n\t// END - Update\n        return Optional.of(cashPoolingRecord)\n                .map(cp -> buildClearingHouseRequest(cashPoolingRecord, config))\n                .flatMap(clearingHouseClient::invokeClearingHouseService)\n                .map(ssdUid -> cashPoolingRecord.toBuilder().withClearingHouseSddUid(UUID.fromString(ssdUid)).build())\n                .map(repository::update)\n                .orElseThrow(() -> new CashPoolingException(\"Failed to save record after creating clearing house SDD for dateKey: \" + cashPoolingRecord.dateKey()));\n    }\n```","CreateDate":"\/Date(1762420057000+0100)\/","Owner":{"ResourceType":"GeneralUser","Id":978,"Login":"aldo.lushkja@satispay.com"},"Project":{"ResourceType":"Project","Id":197811,"Name":"[IT-B] Cash Pooling Library"},"EntityState":{"ResourceType":"EntityState","Id":73,"Name":"Open"}},{"ResourceType":"UserStory","Id":200825,"Name":"Analysis on Loyalty Campaigns Automation","Description":"<!--markdown-->## WHY\nAs we continue to scale Loyalty as a key engagement driver, the Marketing team will increasingly leverage multiplier campaigns to boost Satispay usage during specific periods or at targeted merchants.\n\nTo ensure efficiency and scalability, it’s essential to enable Marketing to autonomously manage campaign setup and execution without relying on manual interventions from other teams.\n\nAutomating this process will:\n\n- Allow faster campaign launches tied to key moments and merchant categories.\n- Reduce operational overhead for the C6 and Engineering teams.\n- Minimise human error and improve campaign management visibility.\n\n## WHAT\n\nDevelop the capability within the Marketing Console to independently create and manage multiplier campaigns for Loyalty.\n\nFunctional Requirements\n\nCampaigns can initially be created by shop_id, offering maximum flexibility.\nIt must be possible to upload a CSV file containing all target shop_ids.\n\nEach campaign setup should include:\n- Start date and end date\n- Multiplier value (e.g., 10x, 20x, etc.)\n\nThe console should display a complete campaign overview, including:\n- Ongoing campaigns\n- Upcoming (scheduled) campaigns\n- Completed campaigns\n\nIt must be possible to:\n- Stop active campaigns before their scheduled end date.\n- Cancel campaigns that have been created but not yet started.","CreateDate":"\/Date(1761822900000+0100)\/","Owner":{"ResourceType":"GeneralUser","Id":978,"Login":"aldo.lushkja@satispay.com"},"Project":{"ResourceType":"Project","Id":147248,"Name":"[IT-B] Consumer Loyalty"},"EntityState":{"ResourceType":"EntityState","Id":73,"Name":"Open"}},{"ResourceType":"UserStory","Id":200392,"Name":"MyBatisImplementation transactional requirements and easier configuration","Description":"<!--markdown-->## WHY\n\nThe current MyBatisCashPoolingRepository does not support transactional operations. \n\nThe mapper.xml is not aligned with the migration column names.\n\nUse convention over configuration in package naming to avoid programatic integration for the client.\n\n## WHAT\n\n1. Make MyBatisCashPoolingRepository support transactions by enhancing the constructor with the SqlSessionFactory. \n\n```java\npublic MyBatisCashPoolingRepository(SqlSessionFactory sqlSessionFactory) {\n        this.sqlSessionFactory = sqlSessionFactory;\n }\n\n   protected SqlSession getSqlSession() {\n        return sqlSessionFactory.openSession();\n    }\n...\n\n    private CashPoolingRecord findById(String uid) {\n        try(SqlSession sqlSession = getSqlSession()){\n            return sqlSession.getMapper(CashPoolingMapper.class).findById(uid);\n        }\n    }\n```\n\n2. Convert mapper-cash-pooling-record.xml to use \"uid\" column names in insert and update.\n\n3. Use the structure above:\n```\npersistence\n\tpostgresql\n\t\tmapper\n```","CreateDate":"\/Date(1761292278000+0200)\/","Owner":{"ResourceType":"GeneralUser","Id":978,"Login":"aldo.lushkja@satispay.com"},"Project":{"ResourceType":"Project","Id":197811,"Name":"[IT-B] Cash Pooling Library"},"EntityState":{"ResourceType":"EntityState","Id":77,"Name":"Done"}},{"ResourceType":"UserStory","Id":200045,"Name":"Monitor Cash Pooling Job Failures","Description":"<!--markdown-->## WHY\n\nThe Cash Pooling Job runs daily at 2:30 AM to process financial transactions for the previous day. If this job fails silently, it could result in:\n  - Unprocessed cash pooling operations\n  - Financial discrepancies that compound over time\n  - Delayed detection of integration issues with the cash pooling service\n  - Manual intervention required to reprocess historical data\n\nWe need proactive monitoring to ensure the job executes successfully and to receive immediate alerts when failures occur, minimizing business impact and reducing mean time to resolution (MTTR).\n\n## WHAT\n\nImplement monitoring and alerting for the Cash Pooling Job with the following capabilities:\n\n1. Failure Alert Monitor (High Priority)\n Alert when: Any CASH_POOLING_JOB_FAILED log appears\n  - Threshold: 1 occurrence\n  - Window: Real-time\n  - Severity: Critical\n  - Use case: Immediate notification when the job fails for any date\n\n2. Success Rate Monitor (Medium Priority)\nAlert when: Success rate drops below 100% over a time period\n  - Metric: Count of CASH_POOLING_JOB_COMPLETED vs CASH_POOLING_JOB_FAILED\n  - Threshold: < 100% success rate\n  - Window: Last 7 days or last 30 executions\n  - Severity: Warning\n  - Use case: Track reliability trend over time\n\n3. Missing Execution Monitor (Medium Priority)\nAlert when: No CASH_POOLING_JOB_STARTED log detected in expected time window\n  - Expected: Daily execution (based on cron: 0 30 2 * * * = 2:30 AM daily)\n  - Threshold: No execution detected within 25 hours\n  - Severity: High\n  - Use case: Detect if job is not running at all (disabled, crashed, etc.)\n\n4. Execution Duration Monitor (Low Priority)\nAlert when: Job takes too long between START and COMPLETED/FAILED\n  - Metric: Time between CASH_POOLING_JOB_STARTED and completion logs\n  - Threshold: > X minutes (you'd need to define based on expected duration)\n  - Severity: Warning\n  - Use case: Detect performance degradation\n\n5. Specific Error Pattern Monitor (Medium Priority)\nAlert when: Specific error patterns appear repeatedly\n  - Pattern: Group by error field in CASH_POOLING_JOB_FAILED\n  - Threshold: Same error type > 3 times in 7 days\n  - Severity: High\n  - Use case: Identify systematic issues vs transient failures\n\n\n  Technical Details:\n  - Log pattern: \"CASH_POOLING_JOB_FAILED - dateKey: {} | error: {}\"\n  - Location: CashPoolingJob.java:51","CreateDate":"\/Date(1761129329000+0200)\/","Owner":{"ResourceType":"GeneralUser","Id":978,"Login":"aldo.lushkja@satispay.com"},"Project":{"ResourceType":"Project","Id":154072,"Name":"[IT-B] Consumer Reward"},"EntityState":{"ResourceType":"EntityState","Id":77,"Name":"Done"}},{"ResourceType":"UserStory","Id":200039,"Name":"Add CashPooling job controller","Description":"<!--markdown-->## WHY\n\nIn case of job failure i want to retry relaunch the job manually or i want to check the current state for a given date key execution.\n\n## WHAT\n\nIn order to be able to launch the job manually create an endpoint inside the JobController class like this:\n\n```java\n    @GET\n    public CashPoolingGetResponseBean getCashPooling(@QueryParam(\"dateKey\") String dateKey) {\n        return jobDelegate.getCashPooling(dateKey);\n    }\n\n    @POST\n    @Path(\"/launch\")\n    public CashPoolingResult cashPooling(@QueryParam(\"dateKey\") String dateKey) {\n        return jobDelegate.executeCashPooling(dateKey);\n    }\n```\n\nThe full url will be something like this: `http://<service-fqdn>:<service_port>/api/v1/jobs/cash_pooling/20251022`","CreateDate":"\/Date(1761127057000+0200)\/","Owner":{"ResourceType":"GeneralUser","Id":978,"Login":"aldo.lushkja@satispay.com"},"Project":{"ResourceType":"Project","Id":154072,"Name":"[IT-B] Consumer Reward"},"EntityState":{"ResourceType":"EntityState","Id":77,"Name":"Done"}},{"ResourceType":"UserStory","Id":199277,"Name":"Add scheduled job","Description":"<!--markdown-->\n## WHY\n\nThe process of cash pooling must be executed at most once each day.\n\n## WHAT\n\nSchedule the daily execution at 02:00 a.m every day by giving the previous day as reference for the calculation.\n\n```java\n\nprivate final CashPoolingService cashPoolingService;\n\n@Scheduled(cron = \"${cash_pooling.job.cron}\")\nvoid executeCashPooling(){\n\tString yesterday = LocalDate.now().minusDays(1).format(DateTimeFormatter.BASIC_ISO_DATE);\n\tcashPoolingService.execute(yesterday);\n}\n```\n ","CreateDate":"\/Date(1760543707000+0200)\/","Owner":{"ResourceType":"GeneralUser","Id":978,"Login":"aldo.lushkja@satispay.com"},"Project":{"ResourceType":"Project","Id":154072,"Name":"[IT-B] Consumer Reward"},"EntityState":{"ResourceType":"EntityState","Id":77,"Name":"Done"}},{"ResourceType":"UserStory","Id":199276,"Name":"Integrate MyBatisCashPoolingRepository implementation","Description":"<!--markdown-->\n## WHY\n\nImplement persistence for the cash pooling record.\n\n## WHAT\n\nUpdate the class **DatabasePostgreSqlConfiguration** in order to be able to configure MyBatis mappers provided by the library.\n\n```java\n    @Bean(name = \"postgreSqlSessionFactory\")\n    public SqlSessionFactory provideSqlSessionForPostgreSql(@Qualifier(\"postgreSqlDataSource\") DataSource dataSource) throws Exception {\n        SqlSessionFactoryBean sessionFactory = new SqlSessionFactoryBean();\n        sessionFactory.setDataSource(dataSource);\n        sessionFactory.setMapperLocations(new PathMatchingResourcePatternResolver().getResources(postgresqlMappersPath)); // add path to mappers here\n        sessionFactory.setConfigLocation(new ClassPathResource(postgresqlConfigPath));\n        sessionFactory.setVfs(MyBatisSpringVFS.class);\n        return sessionFactory.getObject();\n    }\n\n``` ","CreateDate":"\/Date(1760543645000+0200)\/","Owner":{"ResourceType":"GeneralUser","Id":978,"Login":"aldo.lushkja@satispay.com"},"Project":{"ResourceType":"Project","Id":154072,"Name":"[IT-B] Consumer Reward"},"EntityState":{"ResourceType":"EntityState","Id":77,"Name":"Done"}},{"ResourceType":"UserStory","Id":199275,"Name":"Implement the RebalanceAmountProvider","Description":"<!--markdown-->\n## WHY\n\nWe need to calculate the effective amount of money to move for the cash pooling job.\n \n## WHAT\n\nAn example implementation could be something like this:\n\n```java\n\npackage com.satispay.cash_pooling.testutil;\n\nimport com.satispay.cash_pooling.api.RebalanceAmountProvider;\nimport org.slf4j.Logger;\nimport org.slf4j.LoggerFactory;\n\nimport java.time.LocalDate;\nimport java.time.format.DateTimeFormatter;\nimport java.util.HashMap;\nimport java.util.List;\nimport java.util.Map;\nimport java.util.UUID;\n\npublic class RewardBasedAmountProvider implements RebalanceAmountProvider {\n\n    private static final Logger logger = LoggerFactory.getLogger(RewardBasedAmountProvider.class);\n    private static final DateTimeFormatter DATE_FORMATTER = DateTimeFormatter.ofPattern(\"yyyyMMdd\");\n\n    private final Map<String, List<Reward> rewardsByDate;\n\n    public RewardBasedAmountProvider() {\n        this.rewardsByDate = new HashMap<>();\n    }\n\n    public void addReward(String dateKey, UUID userId, Long amountUnit, String description) {\n        rewardsByDate.computeIfAbsent(dateKey, k -> new java.util.ArrayList<>())\n                .add(new Reward(userId, amountUnit, description));\n        logger.debug(\"Added reward for dateKey {}: userId={}, amount={}, description={}\",\n                dateKey, userId, amountUnit, description);\n    }\n\n    public void addRewardsForDate(LocalDate date, List<Reward> rewards) {\n        String dateKey = date.format(DATE_FORMATTER);\n        rewardsByDate.put(dateKey, rewards);\n        logger.debug(\"Added {} rewards for dateKey {}\", rewards.size(), dateKey);\n    }\n\n    @Override\n    public Long computeRebalanceAmount(String dateKey) {\n        List<Reward> rewards = rewardsByDate.get(dateKey);\n\n        if (rewards == null || rewards.isEmpty()) {\n            logger.debug(\"No rewards found for dateKey: {}\", dateKey);\n            return 0L;\n        }\n\n        Long totalAmount = rewards.stream()\n                .mapToLong(Reward::amountUnit)\n                .sum();\n\n        logger.info(\"Computed rebalance amount for dateKey {}: {} (from {} rewards)\",\n                dateKey, totalAmount, rewards.size());\n\n        return totalAmount;\n    }\n\n    public static class Reward {\n        private final UUID userId;\n        private final Long amountUnit;\n        private final String description;\n\n        public Reward(UUID userId, Long amountUnit, String description) {\n            this.userId = userId;\n            this.amountUnit = amountUnit;\n            this.description = description;\n        }\n\n        public UUID userId() {\n            return userId;\n        }\n\n        public Long amountUnit() {\n            return amountUnit;\n        }\n\n        public String description() {\n            return description;\n        }\n\n        @Override\n        public String toString() {\n            return \"Reward{userId=\" + userId + \", amount=\" + amountUnit + \", desc='\" + description + \"'}\";\n        }\n    }\n}\n\n```\n ","CreateDate":"\/Date(1760543546000+0200)\/","Owner":{"ResourceType":"GeneralUser","Id":978,"Login":"aldo.lushkja@satispay.com"},"Project":{"ResourceType":"Project","Id":154072,"Name":"[IT-B] Consumer Reward"},"EntityState":{"ResourceType":"EntityState","Id":77,"Name":"Done"}},{"ResourceType":"UserStory","Id":199274,"Name":"Create required configurations","Description":"<!--markdown-->\n## WHY\n\nIn order to be able to use the newly created service (CashPoolingService) configurations are needed.\n\n## WHAT\n\nUsing Spring @Configuration annotation in class create a CashPoolingConfiguration class that creates the required beans:\n\n```java\n\n@Configuration\npublic class CashPoolingConfiguration {\n    \n    @Autowired\n    private ConfigurationService configurationService;\n\n    @Bean\n    ServiceConfiguration serviceConfiguration(){\n        return new ServiceConfigurationBuilder()\n                .withEnvironment(SdkEnvironmentEnum.DEV)\n                .build();\n    }\n\n    @Bean\n    ClientConfiguration clientConfiguration(){\n        return new ClientConfigurationBuilder()\n                .withServiceName(\"reward\")\n                .build();\n    }\n\n    @Bean\n    CashPoolingConfig config(){\n        return new CashPoolingConfigBuilder()\n                ...\n                .withMandateId(configurationService.get(\"CASH_POOLING_MANDATE_ID\"))\n                .withIbanId(configurationService.get(\"CASH_POOLING_IBAN_ID\"))\n                .withSdkConfiguration(SdkConfiguration.of(serviceConfiguration(), clientConfiguration()))\n                .build();\n    }\n}\n```\n ","CreateDate":"\/Date(1760543466000+0200)\/","Owner":{"ResourceType":"GeneralUser","Id":978,"Login":"aldo.lushkja@satispay.com"},"Project":{"ResourceType":"Project","Id":154072,"Name":"[IT-B] Consumer Reward"},"EntityState":{"ResourceType":"EntityState","Id":77,"Name":"Done"}},{"ResourceType":"UserStory","Id":198477,"Name":"[IAM] - Create new roles and policies for CONSUMER","Description":"<h3>WHY</h3>\r\n\n<ul>\r\n\t<li>new action should be tracked inside an existing IAM authentication policies</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\n<h3>WHAT</h3>\r\n\n<pre><code>curl --location --request PATCH &#39;https&#58;&#47;&#47;internal-admin-api.satispay.aws&#47;core&#47;identity-access-management&#47;v1&#47;access_points&#47;consumer_gateway&#47;roles&#47;consumer_gateway&#58;consumer&#39; &#92;\n--header &#39;Content-Type&#58; application&#47;json&#39; &#92;\n--data &#39;&#123;\n    &quot;policies&quot;&#58; &#91;\n    &#123;\n        &quot;id&quot;&#58; &quot;0&quot;&#44;\n        &quot;effect&quot;&#58; &quot;ALLOW&quot;&#44;\n        &quot;actions&quot;&#58; &#91;\n            &quot;consumer_gateway&#58;all_gateway&quot;\n        &#93;&#44;\n        &quot;resources&quot;&#58; &#91;\n            &quot;consumer_gateway&#58;api&#58;&#42;&#42;&quot;\n        &#93;\n    &#125;&#44;\n    &#123;\n        &quot;id&quot;&#58; &quot;1&quot;&#44;\n        &quot;effect&quot;&#58; &quot;ALLOW&quot;&#44;\n        &quot;actions&quot;&#58; &#91;\n            &quot;consumer_gateway&#58;write_active_process_action&quot;\n        &#93;&#44;\n        &quot;resources&quot;&#58; &#91;\n            &quot;consumer_gateway&#58;api&#58;gateway&#47;v&#42;&#47;active&#47;processes&#47;&#42;&#47;actions&quot;\n        &#93;\n    &#125;&#44;\n    &#123;\n        &quot;id&quot;&#58; &quot;2&quot;&#44;\n        &quot;effect&quot;&#58; &quot;ALLOW&quot;&#44;\n        &quot;actions&quot;&#58; &#91;\n            &quot;consumer_gateway&#58;read_active_bank_iban&quot;\n        &#93;&#44;\n        &quot;resources&quot;&#58; &#91;\n            &quot;consumer_gateway&#58;api&#58;gateway&#47;v&#42;&#47;active&#47;banks&#47;iban&#47;&#42;&quot;\n        &#93;\n    &#125;&#44;\n    &#123;\n        &quot;id&quot;&#58; &quot;3&quot;&#44;\n        &quot;effect&quot;&#58; &quot;ALLOW&quot;&#44;\n        &quot;actions&quot;&#58; &#91;\n            &quot;consumer_gateway&#58;write_active_certificate&quot;\n        &#93;&#44;\n        &quot;resources&quot;&#58; &#91;\n            &quot;consumer_gateway&#58;api&#58;gateway&#47;v&#42;&#47;active&#47;certificates&quot;\n        &#93;\n    &#125;&#44;\n    &#123;\n        &quot;id&quot;&#58; &quot;4&quot;&#44;\n        &quot;effect&quot;&#58; &quot;ALLOW&quot;&#44;\n        &quot;actions&quot;&#58; &#91;\n            &quot;consumer_gateway&#58;read_active_cgm&quo